The osg-cert-scripts-v3 package is a set of scripts created by OSG GOC
to perform host certificate requesting for the OSG PKI.

For questions, comments, info contact goc@opensciencegrid.org.

Contents:
osg-cert-scripts-v3/
 README -                   This file

 cert-request-new.py: Request a single host certificate. Does not
    require you to authenticate with a user certificate to do so.

 cert-retrieve-new.py: Retrieve a single host certificate. Does not
    require you to authentication with a user certificate to do so.

 multi-cert-gridadmin-new.py: Request and retrieve multiple (up to 50)
    host certificates given a list of hostnames in a file. Requires you to
    be a Grid Admin and authenticate with your user certificate.

Installation instructions:

 1) Currently requires python 2.7 (final version will support 2.4 and 2.6)

 2) Current installation is done via svn checkout. A RPM is coming.

svn checkout https://vdt.cs.wisc.edu/svn/software/osg-cert-scripts-v3/trunk/

